race.comment: SOVEREIGN REIGN (4) has been out of the placings the last couple but was a Grade 5 winner (24.80) three back at this track. Good beginner but will need a little luck from a middle draw. Look for sharp improvement here. COOL DISGUISE (7) produced a moderate effort last time when eighth at Wentworth Park over 520m behind Mystical Ethics (30.38) in a Grade 5. Was in the money the start prior. Some good form is emerging from her last run. Worth another chance. LUMEAH STORM (1) ran below best last time finishing fourth (25.27) over 440m at this track from Box 6. Good beginner assisted by the inside draw. Key runner on best form. BANDIT BAY (2) can sneak into the finish.
